interfaces.label: ChromeDocTitle
description: APIs for accessing and updating the document title.

children.label: change
description: Changes the current document title.

children.label: newTitle
description: The new title to set, either a string or string array

children.label: reset
description:
Resets the document title to it's initial value.
(meaning the one present in the title meta at application load.)

children.label: priority
description: Highest priority items are listed at the top of the list of links.

children.label: appName
description: Provide your plugin's name to create a header for separation

children.label: links
description: Creates unified links for sending users to documentation, GitHub, Discuss, or a custom link/button

children.label: content
description: Custom content to occur below the list of links

children.label: linkType
description: Extend EuiButtonEmpty to provide extra functionality

children.label: href
description: URL of the link

children.label: content
description: Content of the button (in lieu of `children`)
signature: boolean | React.ReactChild | React.ReactFragment | React.ReactPortal | null | undefined

children.label: external
description: Opens link in new tab

children.label: linkType
description: Creates a generic give feedback link with comment icon

children.label: href
description:
URL to discuss page.
i.e. `https://discuss.elastic.co/c/${appName}`

children.label: linkType
description: Creates a deep-link to app-specific documentation

children.label: href
description:
URL to documentation page.
i.e. `${ELASTIC_WEBSITE_URL}guide/en/kibana/${DOC_LINK_VERSION}/${appName}.html`,

children.label: linkType
description: Creates a link to a new github issue in the Kibana repo

children.label: labels
description: Include at least one app-specific label to be applied to the new github issue

children.label: title
description: Provides initial text for the title of the issue

interfaces.label: ChromeNavControls
description: {@link ChromeNavControls | APIs} for registering new controls to be displayed in the navigation bar.

children.label: registerLeft
description: Register a nav control to be presented on the bottom-left side of the chrome header.

children.label: registerRight
description: Register a nav control to be presented on the top-right side of the chrome header.

children.label: registerCenter
description: Register a nav control to be presented on the top-center side of the chrome header.

children.label: registerExtension
description: Register an extension to be presented to the left of the top-right side of the chrome header.

children.label: id
description: A unique identifier for looking up links.

children.label: title
description: The title of the application.

children.label: category
description: The category the app lives in

children.label: baseUrl
description: The base route used to open the root of an application.

children.label: url
description: The route used to open the default path and the deep links of an application.

children.label: order
description: An ordinal used to sort nav links relative to one another for display.

children.label: tooltip
description: A tooltip shown when hovering over an app link.

children.label: euiIconType
description:
A EUI iconType that will be used for the app's icon. This icon
takes precedence over the `icon` property.

children.label: icon
description:
A URL to an image file used as an icon. Used as a fallback
if `euiIconType` is not provided.

children.label: href
description: Settled state between `url`, `baseUrl`, and `active`

children.label: disabled
description: Disables a link from being clickable.

children.label: hidden
description: Hides a link from the navigation.

interfaces.label: ChromeNavLinks
description: {@link ChromeNavLinks | APIs} for manipulating nav links.

children.label: getNavLinks$
description: Get an observable for a sorted list of navlinks.

children.label: get
description: Get the state of a navlink at this point in time.

children.label: getAll
description: Get the current state of all navlinks.

children.label: has
description: Check whether or not a navlink exists.

children.label: enableForcedAppSwitcherNavigation
description:
Enable forced navigation mode, which will trigger a page refresh
when a nav link is clicked and only the hash is updated.

children.label: getForceAppSwitcherNavigation$
description: An observable of the forced app switcher state.

interfaces.label: ChromeRecentlyAccessed
description: {@link ChromeRecentlyAccessed | APIs} for recently accessed history.

children.label: add
description: Adds a new item to the recently accessed history.
signature: (link: string, label: string, id: string) => void

children.label: link
description: a relative URL to the resource (not including the {@link HttpStart.basePath | `http.basePath`})

children.label: label
description: the label to display in the UI

children.label: id
description: a unique string used to de-duplicate the recently accessed list.

children.label: get
description: Gets an Array of the current recently accessed history.

children.label: get$
description: Gets an Observable of the array of recently accessed history.

interfaces.label: ChromeStart
description:
ChromeStart allows plugins to customize the global chrome header UI and
enrich the UX with additional information about the current location of the
browser.

children.label: navLinks

children.label: recentlyAccessed

description: {@inheritdoc ChromeDocTitle}

children.label: getIsVisible$
description: Get an observable of the current visibility state of the chrome.

children.label: setIsVisible
description:
Set the temporary visibility for the chrome. This does nothing if the chrome is hidden
by default and should be used to hide the chrome for things like full-screen modes
with an exit button.

children.label: getGlobalHelpExtensionMenuLinks$

children.label: getHelpExtension$

children.label: setHelpExtension

children.label: setHelpSupportUrl
description: Override the default support URL shown in the help menu

children.label: url

children.label: getIsNavDrawerLocked$

children.label: hasHeaderBanner$
description: Get an observable of the current header banner presence state.
